						<summary>

						

						<p>On a slab lying in the Vaṅkēśvarasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">•••• va, Vaiśākha śu. 11.</hi></p>						

						<p>This record in characters of c. 18th century registers the grant of wet land and the income from taxes like <hi rend="italic">bēḍige,</hi> etc., from the lands which belonged to the <hi rend="italic">ijārati</hi> of the donor (name not mentioned) as <hi rend="italic">mānya</hi> for running a <hi rend="italic">chaliveṁdru</hi> (watershed) on the road midway between Dugga and Aḍigoppula to Liṁggaya Tippaya, younger brother of Sōla Ayyapa, for the merit of Dugga Vīrēśvara and Jagapatirāya.</p>						

						</summary>
